name: Joseph J. WALDRON, III, Petitioner v. Jay S. FRIEDENBERG, Magisterial District Judge, Respondent

parties: Joseph J. WALDRON, III, Petitioner v. Jay S. FRIEDENBERG, Magisterial District Judge, Respondent.

opinions.text:
ORDER
PER CURIAM.
AND NOW, this 11th day of December, 2014, the Application for Leave to File Original Process is GRANTED, the Petition for Writ of Mandamus is DENIED, and the Prothonotary is DIRECTED to strike the name of the jurist from the caption.
opinions.author: PER CURIAM.

105 A.3d 661
Joseph J. WALDRON, III, Petitioner v. Jay S. FRIEDENBERG, Magisterial District Judge, Respondent.
No. 166 MM 2014.
Supreme Court of Pennsylvania.
Dec. 11, 2014.
